    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Leadership Needed Now</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bruce Crabtree letter, prompted by Jan 31 Maureeen Dowd Op-Ed column criticizing Sen Hillary Clinton for refusing to say she made bad decision in voting to authorize war, says claim that Congress cannot cut financing for Iraq war while troops are there is dodge for politicians</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mama Hugs Iowa,'' by Maureen Dowd (column, Jan. 31):</p>
        <p>Senator Hillary Rodham Clinton is right. It is the height of irresponsibility to leave it to the next president to get us out of Iraq.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mama Hugs Iowa,'' by Maureen Dowd (column, Jan. 31):</p>
        <p>Senator Hillary Rodham Clinton is right. It is the height of irresponsibility to leave it to the next president to get us out of Iraq.</p>
        <p>So what is she waiting for? She and her Democratic colleagues can get us out right now. The claim that Congress can't cut financing for the war while the troops are in harm's way is nothing but a dodge -- for politicians on both sides of the aisle. Cut financing, and the president will have no choice but to bring the troops home.</p>
        <p>Senator Clinton, get out of Iowa. Go back to Washington and show us that you can be an effective leader now, when we really need it. We can chat later.</p>
        <p>Bruce Crabtree  Jamestown, R.I., Jan. 31, 2007</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
